ATOMIC FIESTA – PRIVACY POLICY

Last updated: 23 February 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how Mid AF Technologies LTD (“we”, “us”, “our”) collects, uses, shares, and protects personal data when you play Atomic Fiesta and use any related online services we operate (the “Services”).

This Policy applies to the Game and Services. It does not replace the privacy policies of your platform provider (e.g., Steam, Epic Games, PlayStation) or other third parties we use (for example, Epic Online Services). Those third parties process personal data under their own policies.

If you have questions, contact: legal@midaf.tech


1. Who is responsible for your data
Data Controller: Mid AF Technologies LTD (United Kingdom)

We are the “controller” for personal data processed when we operate the Services (for example, our servers, moderation tools, support, and account linking logic).

Contact for privacy queries and rights requests: legal@midaf.tech


2. Key definitions
“Personal data” means information that identifies you, or can be used to identify you, directly or indirectly (for example, an account identifier, device identifier, IP address, or voice/chat logs linked to your account).

“UK GDPR” means the UK General Data Protection Regulation and related UK data protection laws, including the Data Protection Act 2018.


3. What personal data we collect and process
The personal data we process depends on what features you use, your platform, and your device. Typical categories include:

3.1 Account and identity data
- Platform account identifiers (e.g., platform user ID)
- Epic Online Services (EOS) identifiers and tokens used for authentication/linking
- In-game identifiers (e.g., character or profile identifiers)
- Player name and avatar (often provided by your platform)

3.2 Gameplay and service data
- Game state and progression (e.g., inventory, unlocks, quest state, stats)
- Matchmaking/session data (e.g., party membership, server assignment)
- Clan membership and clan-related metadata
- Auction house and trade records (listings, bids, trades, timestamps)
- Battle pass-style entitlement/progression data

3.3 Communications and community safety data
- Text chat content (if text chat is enabled), reports, block/mute lists
- Voice chat usage metadata (e.g., participation, session identifiers)
- Moderation records and enforcement history (warnings, suspensions, bans)
- Player reports and evidence submitted by players

3.4 Technical, security, and diagnostics data
- IP address, approximate location inferred from IP (city/region level)
- Device and network information (e.g., device model, OS version, language, time zone)
- Client and server logs, crash reports, performance metrics
- Anti-abuse and security signals (e.g., suspicious activity flags, authentication events)

3.5 Entitlement and purchase verification data
We do not process your payment card details when purchases are handled by your platform/storefront. We may receive and process entitlement information (e.g., “owns product X”, “owns pass Y”) from the platform/storefront to grant access to content.


4. How we use personal data (purposes)
We use personal data for the following purposes:

4.1 Provide and operate the Services
- Authenticate you and link your platform account to EOS identity where applicable
- Provide matchmaking, parties, clans, and other online features
- Store and synchronise your progression and inventory on our servers
- Run the auction house/trading systems and maintain transaction integrity
- Provide customer support and respond to enquiries

4.2 Safety, integrity, and moderation
- Enforce our Terms of Service/EULA and platform rules
- Detect, prevent, and investigate cheating, fraud, scams, exploitation, and abuse
- Moderate text chat (including filtering, review of reports, and enforcement actions)
- Protect players and the Services (including security monitoring and incident response)

4.3 Improve the Game and Services
- Debug issues, fix bugs, analyse performance and stability
- Understand feature usage and balance (telemetry and aggregated analytics)
- Test, develop, and improve content and systems (including public tests)

4.4 Legal and compliance
- Comply with legal obligations, lawful requests, and regulatory requirements
- Establish, exercise, or defend legal claims


5. Lawful bases for processing (UK GDPR)
We rely on one or more lawful bases, depending on the context:

5.1 Contract (UK GDPR Article 6(1)(b))
Processing necessary to provide the Services and perform our contract with you (for example, running servers, saving progression, providing online features, and verifying entitlements).

5.2 Legitimate interests (Article 6(1)(f))
Processing necessary for our legitimate interests in operating a secure, fair, and well-functioning live service game (for example, anti-cheat, fraud prevention, service monitoring, and improving stability), balanced against your rights.

5.3 Legal obligation (Article 6(1)(c))
Processing necessary to comply with legal obligations (for example, responding to lawful requests).

5.4 Consent (Article 6(1)(a)) – where used
In some cases, we may rely on your consent (for example, certain optional features or marketing cookies on websites). Where we rely on consent, you can withdraw it at any time, without affecting processing already carried out.

Special category data: We do not intend to collect “special category” data (e.g., health, biometric identifiers) as part of normal gameplay. If we ever need to process special category data, we will only do so with an appropriate lawful basis under Article 9 UK GDPR (for example, explicit consent or where necessary for legal claims).


6. Voice chat and recording
If voice chat is enabled, voice audio is transmitted to provide the feature. We do not intend to routinely record voice chat.

However, we may record and/or retain voice audio or voice-related data when:
(a) required by applicable law; and/or
(b) reasonably necessary to investigate serious safety issues, abuse, fraud, or security incidents, and to enforce our Terms.

Where we implement voice recording, we intend to provide clear notice in-game and/or in policy materials (for example, feature notices or settings prompts), and we will apply access controls and retention limits appropriate to the purpose.


7. Text chat monitoring and retention
If text chat is enabled, we may:
- monitor, filter, and moderate chat to enforce rules and protect players;
- retain chat logs and related metadata for safety, security, and enforcement; and
- use reports and moderation outcomes to improve detection of abuse and exploitation.

We do not use private chat content to build advertising profiles.


8. Cookies and similar technologies
This Policy primarily covers the Game and Services. Our websites may use cookies and similar technologies for basic functionality, security, and analytics. If we deploy cookies beyond what is strictly necessary, we will present cookie choices or obtain consent where required by law.


9. Who we share personal data with
We may share personal data with:

9.1 Platform and identity providers
- Platform providers (e.g., Steam, PlayStation, Epic) for authentication, entitlement verification, and platform features.
- Epic Online Services (EOS) for identity, authentication, and related online services components.

9.2 Service providers (processors)
We may use third-party service providers to help operate the Services (for example, hosting infrastructure, DDoS protection, logging/crash tools, or voice infrastructure). When we do, we require appropriate contractual protections and process personal data only as necessary to provide the Services.

9.3 Legal, safety, and enforcement
We may disclose information to law enforcement, regulators, courts, or other parties where we believe disclosure is necessary to comply with law, protect safety, prevent fraud, or defend legal claims.

9.4 Corporate transactions
If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, restructuring, or sale of assets, personal data may be shared as part of that transaction, subject to appropriate safeguards and your rights under applicable law.


10. International transfers
Our Services and third-party providers may process personal data outside the UK. Where personal data is transferred internationally, we use appropriate safeguards required by UK GDPR (for example, adequacy regulations, standard contractual clauses, or other approved mechanisms), and we take steps to protect your data.


11. Data retention
We retain personal data only for as long as necessary for the purposes described in this Policy, including to:
- operate the Services and maintain game state;
- enforce rules and resolve disputes;
- comply with legal obligations; and
- protect the safety and integrity of the Services.

Retention periods vary by data type. For example:
- core account and progression data is retained while you have access to the Services and for a reasonable period afterwards (to support account recovery, fraud prevention, and legal compliance);
- chat/moderation logs may be retained for shorter periods, unless needed for investigations or legal claims; and
- technical logs are typically retained for limited periods for security and diagnostics.

We may anonymise or aggregate data and retain it longer for analytics and service improvement.


12. Your rights (UK GDPR)
Depending on your location and the context, you may have the right to:
- access your personal data;
- correct inaccurate data;
- request deletion (where applicable);
- restrict or object to certain processing;
- request data portability (where applicable); and
- withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.

To exercise your rights, contact legal@midaf.tech. We may ask for information to verify your identity and account ownership. Some data may be managed by your platform provider; in those cases, you may need to contact the platform directly.

Complaints: You can lodge a complaint with the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO).


13. Security
We use reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect personal data, including access controls, logging, and security monitoring. No system is perfectly secure; you are responsible for keeping your accounts and devices secure.


14. Children
Atomic Fiesta is distributed with age ratings and access controls set by platform/storefronts and recognised rating systems. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children in a way that is not permitted by applicable law and platform rules. If you believe a child has provided personal data to us inappropriately, contact legal@midaf.tech.


15. Changes to this Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If changes are material, we will use reasonable efforts to notify you via in-game notices, our website, and/or official social media channels. The “Last updated” date at the top shows when this Policy was last revised.


